properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 6 at 2:28AM PST until January 6 at 9:00AM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Areas of north to northeast winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts
up to 50 mph. Strongest between San Marcos Pass and the hills
above Montecito. Winds will diminish later this morning.


* WHERE...Santa Barbara County Mountains.

* WHEN...Until 9 AM PST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Travel may be affected on the San Marcos
Pass and Highway 192 near Montecito.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM PST THIS MORNING... ...HIGH WIND WARNING IS CANCELLED
